gomodel:SYNGO_1375  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig1E shows subcellular fractionation indicating Arf1 and PICK1 in synaptosomes and PSD fractions I and II, while synaptotagmin is abscent. The authors describe ARF1 and PICK1 are \"loosly associated\" with the PSD. p295\n\n25/10/2017 Pim\n- A complex of ARF1/PICK1/AMPAR can be immunoprecipitated from neuronal extracts.. Experimental description: Referred M&M \"Synaptosomes and PSD fractions were prepared from rat brains\", and all other work is also don in rat tissue." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1375" ;
